<subSubSection id="C35967B7FF8AFB34BCBEFC11B9B2F803" pageId="1" pageNumber="362" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BFC343CFF8AFB34BCBEFC11BDDDFABF" blockId="1.[151,1437,898,2003]" pageId="1" pageNumber="362">
<emphasis id="B937E82EFF8AFB34BCBEFC11B804FC6F" bold="true" box="[199,321,934,959]" pageId="1" pageNumber="362">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C434FBFFF8AFB34BD34FC11B8EAFC6E" box="[333,431,934,958]" class="Arachnida" family="Cosmetidae" genus="Ferkeria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opiliones" pageId="1" pageNumber="362" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B937E82EFF8AFB34BD34FC11B8EAFC6E" box="[333,431,934,958]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="362">Ferkeria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is characterized by its gamma 
<typeStatus id="54F88A9EFF8AFB34BF51FC10BA1DFC6F" box="[808,856,935,959]" pageId="1" pageNumber="362">type</typeStatus>
dorsal scutum (
<figureCitation id="137828B9FF8AFB34B863FC11BD24FC6F" box="[1050,1121,934,959]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1671,1693]" captionTargetBox="[151,1423,231,1629]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,195,1649]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Ferkeria spp., in dorsal view: F. flavicoxae sp. nov. A, male holotype, B, female (CBN); F. vestita, C, male (MZUSP 67891), D, female (MZUSP 67892). Scale bars = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/243753/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="362">
Fig. 
<number id="3D8B261BFF8AFB34B82DFC10BD24FC6F" box="[1108,1121,935,959]" pageId="1" pageNumber="362" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
); anterior scutal area with moderately elevated frontal hump and high lateral tubercles (
<figureCitation id="137828B9FF8AFB34BF1EFC7DBAFCFC33" box="[871,953,970,995]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1325,1347]" captionTargetBox="[162,1423,222,1274]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,195,1301]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Ferkeria spp., males in lateral and ventral view: F. flavicoxae sp. nov. holotype, A, ventral, B, lateral; F. vestita (MZUSP 67891), C, ventral, D, lateral. Scale bars = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/243754/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="362">
Figs. 
<number id="3D8B261BFF8AFB34BFD2FC7CBAFCFC33" box="[939,953,971,995]" pageId="1" pageNumber="362" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
B and 
<number id="3D8B261BFF8AFB34B875FC7CBD5EFC33" box="[1036,1051,971,995]" pageId="1" pageNumber="362" value="2.0">2</number>
D); tuberculate and dome-shaped ocularium, with a pair of large tubercles; densely tuberculate carapace; lateral scutal margins with prominent tubercles; unconspicuous scutal grooves; scutal areas IâIV each with a pair of tubercles (enlarged and spiniform on area IV); yellow patches on the sides of the carapace, reaching as far as the scutal area IV (
<figureCitation id="137828B9FF8AFB34B8A9FB81BC65FB9F" box="[1232,1312,1078,1103]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1671,1693]" captionTargetBox="[151,1423,231,1629]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,195,1649]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Ferkeria spp., in dorsal view: F. flavicoxae sp. nov. A, male holotype, B, female (CBN); F. vestita, C, male (MZUSP 67891), D, female (MZUSP 67892). Scale bars = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/243753/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="362">Figs. 1</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="137828B9FF8AFB34B94BFB80BC05FB9F" box="[1330,1344,1079,1103]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1733,1755]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,375,1709]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[151,1436,375,1709]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 8. Ferkeria spp., specimens preserved in ethanol, dorsal view: F. flavicoxae sp. nov., A, male holotype, B, female (CNB); F. vestita, C, male (MZUSP 67891), D, female (MZUSP 67892). Scale bars = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/243760/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="362">8</figureCitation>
and 
<figureCitation id="137828B9FF8AFB34B904FB80BCC8FB9F" box="[1405,1421,1079,1103]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1581,1603]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,700,1556]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[151,1436,700,1557]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 9. Ferkeria spp., live specimens: F. flavicoxae sp. nov., A, male, B, female; F. vestita, C, male, D, female." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/243761/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="362">
<number id="3D8B261BFF8AFB34B904FB80BCC8FB9F" box="[1405,1421,1079,1103]" pageId="1" pageNumber="362" value="9.0">9</number>
</figureCitation>
); posterior scutal margin with pair of prominent spines curved posteriorly; free tergites IâIII with a row of tubercles; median extremity of anal operculum with a large pair of tubercles; isomorphic chelicerae in both sexes, tuberculate bulla (
<figureCitation id="137828B9FF8AFB34BCA6FB15B868FB6B" box="[223,301,1186,1211]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1671,1693]" captionTargetBox="[151,1423,231,1629]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,195,1649]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Ferkeria spp., in dorsal view: F. flavicoxae sp. nov. A, male holotype, B, female (CBN); F. vestita, C, male (MZUSP 67891), D, female (MZUSP 67892). Scale bars = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/243753/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="362">Figs. 1</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="137828B9FF8AFB34BD45FB14B80FFB6B" box="[316,330,1187,1211]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1325,1347]" captionTargetBox="[162,1423,222,1274]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,195,1301]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Ferkeria spp., males in lateral and ventral view: F. flavicoxae sp. nov. holotype, A, ventral, B, lateral; F. vestita (MZUSP 67891), C, ventral, D, lateral. Scale bars = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/243754/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="362">2</figureCitation>
B and 
<number id="3D8B261BFF8AFB34BDEDFB14B8E6FB6B" box="[404,419,1187,1211]" pageId="1" pageNumber="362" value="2.0">2</number>
D); pedipalpal femur with dorsal tubercles and a prominent row of ventral tubercles (
<figureCitation id="137828B9FF8AFB34B91DFB15B9E1FB0F" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1893,1915]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,569,1853]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1436,569,1853]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 5. Ferkeria spp. pedipalp of males in lateral view (femur â tarsus) and in detail of tibia and tarsus, respectively: A, B, F. flavicoxae sp. nov. (MZUSP 67893); C, D, F. vestita (MZUSP 67892). Scale bars = 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/243757/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="362">
Figs. 
<number id="3D8B261BFF8AFB34BCEEFB71B9E1FB0F" box="[151,164,1222,1247]" pageId="1" pageNumber="362" value="5.0">5</number>
</figureCitation>
A and 
<number id="3D8B261BFF8AFB34BC88FB71B9BAFB0F" box="[241,255,1222,1247]" pageId="1" pageNumber="362" value="5.0">5</number>
C); wide, dimorphic coxa IV (large in male), reaching the posterior scutal margin, tuberculate and with a prolateral apical apophysis (
<figureCitation id="137828B9FF8AFB34BDAAFB5DBB51FAD3" box="[467,532,1258,1283]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1671,1693]" captionTargetBox="[151,1423,231,1629]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,195,1649]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Ferkeria spp., in dorsal view: F. flavicoxae sp. nov. A, male holotype, B, female (CBN); F. vestita, C, male (MZUSP 67891), D, female (MZUSP 67892). Scale bars = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/243753/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="362">
Fig. 
<number id="3D8B261BFF8AFB34BE7EFB5CBB51FAD3" box="[519,532,1259,1283]" pageId="1" pageNumber="362" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
); femur IV dorsally curved; femoraâmetatarsi IâIV covered with thick tubercles (
<figureCitation id="137828B9FF8AFB34BCE6FAB9B9A6FAF7" box="[159,227,1294,1319]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1453,1475]" captionTargetBox="[164,1415,389,1412]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,375,1428]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Ferkeria spp., male leg IV (trochanter â patella) in dorsal and ventral views: F. flavicoxae sp. nov. holotype, A, dorsal, B, ventral; F. vestita (MZUSP 67891), C, dorsal, D, ventral. Scale bars = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/243755/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="362">
Fig. 
<number id="3D8B261BFF8AFB34BCADFAB8B9A6FAF7" box="[212,227,1295,1319]" pageId="1" pageNumber="362" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
); maleâs basitarsi I and III dimorphic, enlarged; leg tarsi III and IV smooth; penis without dorsal process of glans, dorsally wrinkled glans base, stylus with gonopore and keels placed on apex, without ventral apical keels and ventral apice of the truncus with two pairs of small macrosetae group B (
<figureCitation id="137828B9FF8AFB34BF8EFAE1BD01FABF" box="[1015,1092,1366,1391]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1983,2005]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,683,1958]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,673,1958]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 6. Ferkeria spp., penis in dorsal and ventral views: F. flavicoxae sp. nov. (MZUSP 67893) A, dorsal, B, ventral; F. vestita (MZUSP 67891), C, dorsal, D, ventral. Scale bars = 0.1 mm (A, B) and 0.05 mm (C, D)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/243758/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="362">
Figs. 
<number id="3D8B261BFF8AFB34B84FFAE1BD01FABF" box="[1078,1092,1366,1391]" pageId="1" pageNumber="362" value="6.0">6</number>
</figureCitation>
and 
